00:19:10.860 --> 00:19:12.360 align:middle line:90%
gain their own consciousness?

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:13.920 align:middle line:90%
Can start becoming self-aware.

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:18.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: OK, so self-awareness
itself is a tricky thing.

00:19:18.300 --> 00:19:20.700 align:middle line:84%
And one of the reasons
it took decades

00:19:20.700 --> 00:19:24.250 align:middle line:84%
to make any progress in
AI is a very simple one.

00:19:24.250 --> 00:19:25.380 align:middle line:90%
It's all linguistic.

00:19:25.380 --> 00:19:28.590 align:middle line:84%
We don't even agree on what
the definitions for thought

00:19:28.590 --> 00:19:30.700 align:middle line:90%
and awareness and memory are.

00:19:30.700 --> 00:19:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And so this was one of the
major stumbling blocks.

00:19:33.360 --> 00:19:35.490 align:middle line:84%
Now, we've pretty
much agreed that we

00:19:35.490 --> 00:19:38.190 align:middle line:84%
can make things that function
very much like neurons

00:19:38.190 --> 00:19:40.110 align:middle line:90%
and very much like brain tissue.

00:19:40.110 --> 00:19:42.270 align:middle line:84%
And in fact,
building neural nets,

00:19:42.270 --> 00:19:44.190 align:middle line:84%
we've discovered
that when they make

00:19:44.190 --> 00:19:46.500 align:middle line:84%
failures occur in
them, many of them

00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.150 align:middle line:84%
model failures in
the human brain,

00:19:49.150 --> 00:19:51.240 align:middle line:90%
such as types of aphasias.

00:19:51.240 --> 00:19:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And so this is one
of the indicators

00:19:53.460 --> 00:19:56.940 align:middle line:84%
that the neural nets are very
close to what nature is doing,

00:19:56.940 --> 00:19:59.040 align:middle line:84%
and we learned a lot
from making models.

00:19:59.040 --> 00:20:01.680 align:middle line:84%
The problem with neural
nets is a simple one.

00:20:01.680 --> 00:20:05.340 align:middle line:84%
If you design and intentionally
build a specific device

00:20:05.340 --> 00:20:10.410 align:middle line:84%
to act as a thinking system,
when you use neural nets,

00:20:10.410 --> 00:20:12.420 align:middle line:84%
you have no idea what's
happening inside it

00:20:12.420 --> 00:20:15.098 align:middle line:84%
and very little way
of interpreting it.

00:20:15.098 --> 00:20:16.890 align:middle line:84%
If you try to build
the same machine again,

00:20:16.890 --> 00:20:19.020 align:middle line:84%
you're going to get a
different system because they

00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:21.795 align:middle line:90%
learn at random, just as we do.

00:20:21.795 --> 00:20:24.270 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: With
experience and data input.

00:20:24.270 --> 00:20:25.413 align:middle line:90%
>> Shults: Exactly.

00:20:25.413 --> 00:20:27.330 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I mean, you
could argue most humans

00:20:27.330 --> 00:20:28.130 align:middle line:90%
aren't self-aware.

00:20:28.130 --> 00:20:31.090 align:middle line:84%
So maybe this is a
conversation before its time.

00:20:31.090 --> 00:20:32.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: Well, and
that's a tricky one.

00:20:32.850 --> 00:20:35.940 align:middle line:84%
You could do another-- you
could do hours on that alone.

00:20:35.940 --> 00:20:37.110 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:20:37.110 --> 00:20:40.950 align:middle line:84%
So your perspective
from what you understand

00:20:40.950 --> 00:20:44.370 align:middle line:84%
