some kind to help us out

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:47.640 align:middle line:90%
around the house.

00:20:47.640 --> 00:20:48.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Shults: Absolutely.

00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:50.280 align:middle line:84%
But the big question
is, if it's smart enough

00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:53.480 align:middle line:84%
to understand what you're
instructing it to do,

00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:56.240 align:middle line:84%
why would it want to do
what you tell it and not

00:20:56.240 --> 00:20:57.163 align:middle line:90%
what it wants to do?

00:20:57.163 --> 00:20:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well,
that's the thing,

00:20:58.580 --> 00:21:00.860 align:middle line:84%
the whole notion
of will and desire.

00:21:00.860 --> 00:21:04.070 align:middle line:84%
So how do you write a
program around that does not

00:21:04.070 --> 00:21:07.600 align:middle line:84%
include will and desire,
that literally only includes

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:08.400 align:middle line:90%
response?

00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:11.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: Well, even if you
didn't know the answer to that

00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:13.370 align:middle line:84%
one, there's one tricky
thing you can do,

00:21:13.370 --> 00:21:17.752 align:middle line:84%
and that is to build in a
desire to be happy working.

00:21:17.752 --> 00:21:19.040 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, there you go.

00:21:19.040 --> 00:21:20.748 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: Boy, there's
a slippery slope,

00:21:20.748 --> 00:21:24.390 align:middle line:84%
because then it's only a few
minutes before somebody says,

00:21:24.390 --> 00:21:25.970 align:middle line:84%
hey, we could do
this to people too.

00:21:25.970 --> 00:21:28.280 align:middle line:90%
And that's what scares people.

00:21:28.280 --> 00:21:29.605 align:middle line:90%
It sums it up in a nutshell.

00:21:29.605 --> 00:21:32.300 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, in one of
those two shows, I talked about,

00:21:32.300 --> 00:21:34.175 align:middle line:84%
the Russian one called
"Better Than Us," of course,

00:21:34.175 --> 00:21:35.217 align:middle line:90%
it's absolutely gorgeous.

00:21:35.217 --> 00:21:38.510 align:middle line:84%
Drop dead, gorgeous, beautiful
robot comes into this family,

00:21:38.510 --> 00:21:40.340 align:middle line:84%
and you can-- anyone
who wants to watch

00:21:40.340 --> 00:21:41.780 align:middle line:84%
