00:22:20.450 --> 00:22:22.025 align:middle line:84%
I find it fascinating
personally.

00:22:22.025 --> 00:22:24.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: I think that one of
the things we have to face is

00:22:24.740 --> 00:22:28.130 align:middle line:84%
that most people at some point
can't even manage their own

00:22:28.130 --> 00:22:29.510 align:middle line:90%
lives properly.

00:22:29.510 --> 00:22:32.450 align:middle line:84%
We all have
limitations and issues,

00:22:32.450 --> 00:22:36.230 align:middle line:84%
but nobody wants to admit
to those limitations.

00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:39.675 align:middle line:84%
And then we're going to trust a
group of limited, flawed humans

00:22:39.675 --> 00:22:40.550 align:middle line:90%
to create something--

00:22:40.550 --> 00:22:41.810 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: To design a program--

00:22:41.810 --> 00:22:42.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Shults: --of perfection.

00:22:42.470 --> 00:22:43.270 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:22:43.270 --> 00:22:45.615 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: That, that is an
