00:22:57.780 --> 00:23:00.680 align:middle line:90%
But this is a little different.

00:23:00.680 --> 00:23:03.242 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about it-- who
they are, what they're doing,

00:23:03.242 --> 00:23:04.700 align:middle line:84%
and how far they've
gotten with it.

00:23:04.700 --> 00:23:06.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Shults: Well, one of
the early founding members

00:23:06.980 --> 00:23:09.890 align:middle line:84%
of Synchron actually worked
with Neuralink on the project

00:23:09.890 --> 00:23:10.710 align:middle line:90%
for a while.

00:23:10.710 --> 00:23:13.640 align:middle line:84%
And when he left, he had
some dissatisfaction,

00:23:13.640 --> 00:23:16.130 align:middle line:84%
which I won't go into
any of the details.

00:23:16.130 --> 00:23:19.310 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is he got
to work with Synchron.

00:23:19.310 --> 00:23:21.050 align:middle line:84%
And Synchron had a
slightly different way

00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:22.730 align:middle line:90%
of approaching it.

00:23:22.730 --> 00:23:25.340 align:middle line:84%
With Neuralink, you
must open the skull

00:23:25.340 --> 00:23:29.193 align:middle line:84%
to get the chip in contact
with a portion of the brain.

00:23:29.193 --> 00:23:31.610 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times, you're
going to look at the area known

00:23:31.610 --> 00:23:33.410 align:middle line:90%
where the homunculus resides.

00:23:33.410 --> 00:23:35.120 align:middle line:90%
It's a model of the body.

00:23:35.120 --> 00:23:37.210 align:middle line:84%
And that way, it can
read information from it

00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:39.252 align:middle line:84%
and determine what the
movements are going to be,

00:23:39.252 --> 00:23:40.640 align:middle line:90%
make predictions.

00:23:40.640 --> 00:23:43.250 align:middle line:10%
Synchron has a
different type of device

00:23:43.250 --> 00:23:47.690 align:middle line:10%
that actually works in the
same way a cardiac stent would.

00:23:47.690 --> 00:23:51.500 align:middle line:84%
The electrode array is
inserted through an artery

00:23:51.500 --> 00:23:52.550 align:middle line:90%
into the brain.

00:23:52.550 --> 00:23:54.740 align:middle line:90%
They steer it into the location.

00:23:54.740 --> 00:23:58.730 align:middle line:84%
They implant this stent,
and it makes the connections

00:23:58.730 --> 00:23:59.570 align:middle line:90%
through there.

00:23:59.570 --> 00:24:02.270 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually
go home after 48 hours

00:24:02.270 --> 00:24:03.140 align:middle line:90%
after the surgery.

00:24:03.140 --> 00:24:03.940 align:middle line:90%
It's very--

00:24:03.940 --> 00:24:05.705 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Did you say the
blood flowing through the stent?

00:24:05.705 --> 00:24:06.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Shults: That's correct.

00:24:06.950 --> 00:24:08.060 align:middle line:90%
It's like a collar.

00:24:08.060 --> 00:24:10.070 align:middle line:84%
You can slightly
expand the blood vessel

00:24:10.070 --> 00:24:12.980 align:middle line:84%
without obscuring the
blood flow or obstructing,

00:24:12.980 --> 00:24:14.090 align:middle line:90%
and I should say.

00:24:14.090 --> 00:24:18.770 align:middle line:84%
So they actually implanted
the devices, the test devices

00:24:18.770 --> 00:24:22.160 align:middle line:84%
from Synchron in 2018
in an Australian man

00:24:22.160 --> 00:24:24.590 align:middle line:84%
who very rapidly learned
how to send texts

00:24:24.590 --> 00:24:26.130 align:middle line:90%
by thinking about it.

00:24:26.130 --> 00:24:28.820 align:middle line:84%
So this is a direct
and very useful

00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:31.670 align:middle line:84%
application particularly
for people who are locked in

00:24:31.670 --> 00:24:34.740 align:middle line:84%
or are unable to move or unable
to communicate in any way.

00:24:34.740 --> 00:24:38.510 align:middle line:84%
If you can get somebody who is
totally paralyzed to the point

00:24:38.510 --> 00:24:40.940 align:middle line:84%
where they can communicate
by sending texts,

00:24:40.940 --> 00:24:42.553 align:middle line:84%
you've taken a
major step forward

00:24:42.553 --> 00:24:44.720 align:middle line:84%
in improving their quality
of life and understanding

00:24:44.720 --> 00:24:45.785 align:middle line:90%
what's going on.

00:24:45.785 --> 00:24:48.290 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, I think what
comes to mind is a friend

00:24:48.290 --> 00:24:51.920 align:middle line:84%
of mine, dear friend,
lifelong friend.

00:24:51.920 --> 00:24:54.470 align:middle line:84%
Interesting, this gets
into a lot of stuff.

00:24:54.470 --> 00:24:56.060 align:middle line:84%
When she retired
didn't really want

00:24:56.060 --> 00:24:58.070 align:middle line:84%
to but her husband
wanted her to.

00:24:58.070 --> 00:24:59.510 align:middle line:90%
